wikipedia_page.main: Alfred Carey Wollaston Rose (1884 – 9 April 1971) was the sixth Bishop of Dover, England, in the modern era, from 1935 to 1956.

response: Rose was the son of Alfred Rose, former Bishop of Dover and Lois Juliet. He was educated at Marlborough College and Christ Church, Oxford. In 1946 he married Elisabeth Mackenzie, daughter of Reverend Cyril Lewis, Gilston; they had two sons and three daughters.British Diplomatic Oral History Programme
